I discovered a weirdness with the 7809 voltage regulator
it seems when you have its output going into a 7805 it causes instability to programmable oscilators
the issue caused a wavering effect in the carrier on the AM transmitter and also resulted in the 25 Hz stereo pilot tone fluctuating a bit
so its back to crystals when I want to run full power

a highly flexable processor

also for FM mono transmitters FM stereo multiplex encoding
you can build a very simple two transistor FM transmitter and use Stereo Tool for generating stereo and RDS along with premphasis

-!- Taiyaki|„Åü„ÅÑÁÑº„Åç|, literally "baked sea bream" is a Japanese fish-shaped cake. The most common filling is red bean paste that is made from sweetened azuki beans. Other common fillings may be custard, chocolate, or cheese. Some shops even sell taiyaki with okonomiyaki, gyoza filling, or a sausage inside.

a codec is a piece of hardware or software that encodes and decodes audio or video information
so saying "I HAVE A MOV THAT WONT OPEN!!!" isn't very informative at all. You have specified the container [mov], but not the compression schemes inside it [h264,sorenson] for video, or [aiff,ima,aac] for video.
which is what really matters.
plus you can find some oddball codecs used in some containers
for example I have seen Windows Media Video in the AVI container
containers [avi,mov,mp4] CONTAIN codecs which use compression schemes [xvid,h264,sorenson] , to store stuff. those are only a few examples. so do you get it now?
hmm..
_help help
darn
you may be able to change codec independent of container using some tools, and vice-versa,
a process known as demuxing
splitting the streams within a container into individual files or streams

_help fail
